                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>563</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>##</strong><strong>$a</strong>Late 16th century blind-tooled centrepiece binding,
                                             dark brown calf.<strong>$u</strong>&lt;URI&gt;<strong>$5</strong>StEdNL
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$u - Uniform Resource Identifier</strong> <div class="description">Uniform Resource Identifier (URI), for example a URL or URN, which provides
                              electronic access data in a standard syntax. This data may be used for automated
                              access to an electronic item using one of the Internet protocols.
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
